<br>
We pride ourselves greatly on our &quot;melting pot&quot; (its the one massive cultural difference between us and Canada - we integrate every culture, they accept every culture).  What is this horrific american culture that the europeans sneer at and the islamic world shuns?  It's nothing more than a culture of people who have come to accept each others differences - I'd go so far as to say it's a PREVIEW of the &quot;global society&quot; or morality which I spoke about before.  For the last 100 years, we've taken in every imaginable people and learned to live with them (and they've learned to add their cultural uniqueness to our own). <br>
<br>
This is why Americans are proud to be americans (for as much as that pride seems to wholly annoy the rest of the world <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )... nobody on this board who is posting comes from probably more than 120 years or so of family in the US, and some of you may be immigrants yourselves, or first generation.  Seeing the culture work so well together is a real source of national unity and pride, and its why WE sneer at the europeans who maintain cultural differences and borders like they're defending their lives.  Watching the French (for example) ban the use of English on the Internet and other things just seems.. well, in WA's words, uncivilized, a generation or 2 behind.<br>
<br>
Where's this rant going?  Oh yeah - Cal, the fact that you believe your culture to be superior and dominant over all others, instead of looking to work with them and maybe even learn from them, is the most un-american thing i've read all day.<br>
