Oh, and Cald, honestly - most western 'tradition' comes straight (as in do-not-pass-go, do-not-collect-$200) right from ancient Rome.  Our system of law, our government, even our political structure are direct descendants of an empire which was a whole lot bigger and a whole lot more successful than anything around today.<br>
<br>
Corruption eventually brought it down, and I'm calling the same shenanigans on Bush and company, using scare tactics and the possibility of some evidence of something they're not quite sure of to further their interests.<br>
<br>
Christian influence brought about only one thing in the western world's history, and that was the Dark Ages.  The church made damn sure to keep the common people down, because they were a whole lot easier to control.  The &quot;rebirth&quot; of science, art, and education is what led us back to western society of today, which America is only the latest, greatest example of.<br>
<br>
So before you go looking to the Good Book to thank for America's amazing success and world dominance, check out the civilization who killed Jesus and compare what they did, and what led to their downfall, to what has transpired in the last 200 years or so.  You may be surprised. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuwene>Tuwene</A> at: 2/24/03 7:59:19 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg>TheTribunal.org</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36>Reality Sinks In</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org/">Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <!-- .. -->
